Long name: Moisture in Upper Portion of Soil Column
description: The mass of water in all phases in the upper 10cm of the  soil layer.
comment: the mass of water in all phases in a thin surface soil layer.
cell_methods: area: mean where land time: mean

description: the mass per unit area  (summed over all soil layers) of water in all phases.
comment: the mass per unit area  (summed over all soil layers) of water in all phases.
cell_methods: area: mean where land time: mean

description: The mass per unit area (summed over all model layers) of frozen water.
comment: the mass (summed over all all layers) of frozen water.
cell_methods: area: mean where land time: mean

description: The total surface run off leaving the land portion of the grid cell (excluding drainage through the base of the soil model).
comment: the total surface runoff leaving the land portion of the grid cell.
cell_methods: area: mean where land time: mean

description: The total run-off (including drainage through the base of the soil model) per unit area leaving the land portion of the grid cell.
comment: the total runoff (including "drainage" through the base of the soil model) leaving the land portion of the grid cell.
cell_methods: area: mean where land time: mean

description: The precipitation flux that is intercepted by the vegetation canopy (if present in model) before reaching the ground.
comment: the precipitation flux that is intercepted by the vegetation canopy (if present in model) before reaching the ground.
cell_methods: area: mean where land time: mean

description: The canopy evaporation and sublimation (if present in model); may include dew formation as a negative flux.
comment: the canopy evaporation+sublimation (if present in model).
cell_methods: area: mean where land time: mean

description: Water evaporation from soil (including sublimation).
comment: includes sublimation.
cell_methods: area: mean where land time: mean

description: Transpiration (may include dew formation as a negative flux).
cell_methods: area: mean where land time: mean

description: The mass of water in all phases, including ice, in soil layers.  Report as missing for grid cells with no land.
comment: in each soil layer, the mass of water in all phases, including ice.  Reported as "missing" for grid cells occupied entirely by "sea"
cell_methods: area: mean where land time: mean
structure title: Temporal mean, Global field on soil levels [XY-S] [amnla-tmn]

description: Temperature of each soil layer. Reported as missing for grid cells with no land.
comment: Temperature of each soil layer.  Reported as "missing" for grid cells occupied entirely by "sea".
structure title: Temporal mean, Global field on soil levels [XY-S] [amnla-tmn]

description: Percentage of entire grid cell  that is covered by trees.

description: Percentage of entire grid cell  that is covered by bare soil.

Long name: Fraction of Grid Cell that is Land but Neither Vegetation-Covered nor Bare Soil

comment: fraction of entire grid cell  that is land and is covered by "non-vegetation" and "non-bare-soil" (e.g., urban, ice, lakes, etc.)

description: Fraction of entire grid cell  that is covered by burnt vegetation.
comment: fraction of entire grid cell  that is covered by burnt vegetation.
a ratio obtained by dividing the total upper leaf surface area of vegetation by the (horizontal) surface area of the land on which it grows.

description: Percentage of grid cell area occupied by different model vegetation/land cover categories. The categories may differ from model to model, depending on each model's subgrid land cover category definitions. Categories may include natural vegetation, anthropogenic vegetation, bare soil, lakes, urban areas, glaciers, etc. Sum of all should equal the fraction of the grid-cell that is land.
comment: The categories may differ from model to model, depending on their  PFT definitions.   This may include natural PFTs, anthropogenic PFTs, bare soil, lakes, urban areas, etc.   Sum of all should equal the fraction of the grid-cell that is land.
